. CPO doesn’t integrate lasers into the package. Both Broadcom and NVIDIA use external pluggable laser modules (ELSFP standard) that feed light into the silicon photonics engines. Bailly uses 16 per switch; Quantum-X manages all 144 × 800G channels with just 18. ￼

10,000 Foxconn switch trays = ~160,000 ELSFP modules this year at Bailly-equivalent counts.

The ELSFP supply chain is a two-horse race. $LITE announced its largest PO ever for ELSFPs and $COHR announced one too. ￼ Both targeting volume into scale-up hardware by 2027."}}}, "rest_id": "2060467911597408579", "source": "<a href="http://twitter.com/download/iphone" rel="nofollow">Twitter for iPhone</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "218", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}

